Just seeing her eat like that will give me indigestion.

4
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:02,670
Gosh, is she determined or foolish?

5
00:02:07,410 --> 00:02:09,120
Doing as much as others

6
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:12,160
won't let me live like others.

7
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:14,690
I knew that early on, but...

8
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:17,440
Let's start the operation.

9
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:19,230
Scalpel.

10
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,500
- What's this?
- Why did she faint?

11
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:33,110
Are you okay?

12
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:34,400
Hyo Ri!

13
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,890
Ms. Lee Hyo Ri.

14
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,220
Are you here alone?

15
00:02:39,220 --> 00:02:40,720
Yes.

16
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:48,370
The CT and MRI scans detected a brain tumor.

17
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:49,770
"Tumor"?

18
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:52,490
It's not metastatic. It appears localized.

19
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:54,800
We'll know the details after a biopsy.

20
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:57,800
So, you need surgery first.

21
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,930
But as much as I tried,

22
00:03:03,930 --> 00:03:07,170
exactly as much,

23
00:03:08,140 --> 00:03:11,640
I thought I'd get a chance, too.

24
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:18,360
It's Patient Kim Min Ji, 27 years old.

25
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,890
She was hospitalized due to sudden quadriplegia.

26
00:03:20,890 --> 00:03:24,400
The test revealed a tumor in her brainstem.

27
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:30,600
Gosh! Hello, Doctor.

28
00:03:31,410 --> 00:03:33,720
How are you feeling?

29
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,890
She doesn't eat because she's worried.

30
00:03:35,890 --> 00:03:38,250
She's such a troublemaker, Doctor.

31
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:39,550
Mom.

32
00:03:39,550 --> 00:03:43,220
Don't say stuff like that to the doctor.

33
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:45,380
While caring for her,

34
00:03:45,380 --> 00:03:48,800
we're telling her to be strong.

35
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:51,500
I said she can count on you.

36
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,760
Yes.

37
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:55,120
Don't worry, and relax your mind, as your father said.

38
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,460
Eat the food your mother gives you

39
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:59,470
and care for yourself.

40
00:03:59,470 --> 00:04:02,570
- Yes, thank you.
- Thank you.

41
00:04:16,210 --> 00:04:20,270
With this misfortune that's on another level,

42
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:22,780
I hopelessly...

43
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:27,560
became afraid.

44
00:04:28,530 --> 00:04:30,690
I became sad.

45
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:34,040
I'm home!

46
00:04:47,050 --> 00:04:49,160
Have you eaten?

47
00:04:51,110 --> 00:04:53,150
How old are you?

48
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:56,480
You should feed yourself if I'm home late.

49
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:59,770
It'd be nice if you made some for me, too.

50
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,810
Let's see what we have.

51
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:11,100
There it is.

52
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,100
I...

53
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:24,420
- need to tell you—
- You know I live for you, right?

54
00:05:25,590 --> 00:05:27,000
Become a great doctor soon,

55
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:31,500
so I can retire before 50 and enjoy life while shopping.

56
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:42,550
Hey!

57
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:45,290
You can't break the door like that.

58
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:53,140
Guilt mixed with sadness

59
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:56,100
became a childish tantrum,

60
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:59,800
anger, and tears.

61
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:03,510
And it hurt us more.

62
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:16,100
Ms. Lee Hyo Ri's guardian, please come in.

63
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,760
Okay.

64
00:06:20,570 --> 00:06:21,870
Awake surgery is appropriate

65
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:24,240
when you cut out a tumor

66
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:27,050
that's melded into the brain.

67
00:06:27,050 --> 00:06:29,700
Her tumor is small,

68
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:33,230
but it's located near a highly functional part of the brain.

69
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:35,420
So, through the awake surgery,

70
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:37,930
we'll safeguard important parts of the brain

71
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:39,720
and remove the tumor.

72
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:42,560
Yes. She'll receive all necessary treatments.

73
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:46,180
We trust you and will get all the treatments you mentioned.

74
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:50,700
Please schedule her surgery sooner.

75
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,890
Well,

76
00:06:52,890 --> 00:06:56,300
I will schedule it as soon as possible,

77
00:06:56,300 --> 00:07:00,270
and move it earlier if I can.

78
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,100
Thank you.

79
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:03,870
Doctor,

80
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,880
as for the treatment cost...

81
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:09,240
How much will it be?

82
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:28,280
Don't you want to visit Hyo Ri?

83
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,040
I'm going to HQ now.

84
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:33,010
You can't even work because of the audit. Why go?

85
00:07:33,010 --> 00:07:35,090
You heard the doctor, right?

86
00:07:35,090 --> 00:07:38,560
I must pay for her treatment. I can't get fired.

87
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,510
Will you beg the owner or something?

88
00:07:40,510 --> 00:07:42,300
That piece of work?

89
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:45,100
No matter what it takes, I'll survive at work

90
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:48,510
and give her all the good treatments she can get.

91
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,590
I'll go now.

92
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:52,880
Hey, please call Hyo Ri. Okay?

93
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:22,630
Sir.

94
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,400
My sister-in-law is a nurse at Mungyeong Hospital.

95
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:34,620
- Should I ask her?
- Yes, if I need help later.

96
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:37,310
How are things with the Audit Team?

97
00:08:37,310 --> 00:08:40,880
They seem to think it was Manager Jang based on the circumstances.

98
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:44,980
But the owner is so unpredictable.

99
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,200
- Let's try talking to him.
- Yes.

100
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,040
Here he comes.

101
00:09:01,730 --> 00:09:04,210
I see you often lately, Manager Lee.

102
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:06,000
Are you feeling anxious?

103
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:09,800
I get to see you often because of it. It's so nice.

104
00:09:12,210 --> 00:09:13,570
Hey,

105
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:16,590
try harder when you lie.

106
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:19,810
You can't be successful because you can't do that.

107
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:24,840
Come on. Fill it up with Spam.

108
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,680
You can't even tell Spam and sausage apart.

109
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,600
Just give it to me. Give it to me.

110
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,340
Give it to me.

111
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:40,690
Sir, regarding Manager Lee's audit—

112
00:09:40,690 --> 00:09:42,550
Yes, the audit.

113
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:45,300
I spoke with the Audit Team.

114
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:47,680
You must take some responsibility.

115
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,160
Pardon?

116
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:51,780
Sir, you're joking. Right?

117
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:55,240
It's your fault for not catching it.

118
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,870
Just accept it and be done with it.

119
00:09:56,870 --> 00:09:59,650
You went through a lot. Go on and eat.

120
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:02,000
Sir, it's so unfair for her—

121
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,990
Why are you butting in again?

122
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:07,100
You don't know when to butt in or not, do you?

123
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,600
It's not that, Sir.

124
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:11,370
Based on her circumstances, if she can't work—

125
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:12,930
"Circumstances"? What circumstances?

126
00:10:12,930 --> 00:10:15,400
Who in this country doesn't have circumstances?

127
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:18,300
Manager Lee is still young. She can quickly find another job.

128
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:19,730
Right.

129
00:10:19,730 --> 00:10:22,800
You said your daughter goes to a top medical school.

130
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,300
You seem to have no luck with a husband.

131
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:27,310
Let your daughter pamper you and play rich.

132
00:10:27,310 --> 00:10:28,900
Gosh, I'm jealous.

133
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:32,400
- Gosh, Sir.
- Did I just get fired?

134
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:38,500
- I'll give you severance pay—
- Whatever.

135
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,700
- Did you just fire me?
- What did you say?

136
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:44,280
How can you come into work at 11:00 a.m. every day? Do you know the work hours?

137
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,450
Even kindergarteners need to arrive by 9:00 a.m.

138
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:49,070
You show up late, and you bully the employees

139
00:10:49,070 --> 00:10:51,420
who left home while it was still dark out.

140
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:55,200
You call whomever's below you "this bastard" and "that bastard."

141
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:58,410
You'll pay me severance pay?

142
00:10:58,410 --> 00:10:59,930
Wake up.

143
00:10:59,930 --> 00:11:02,400
That's my right, not your charity.

144
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,160
You...

145
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,440
You're crazy, right? Oh, right.

146
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,330
It's because you got fired, right?

147
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:10,500
Listen carefully. Okay?

148
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:15,600
Do you know why people tolerate your overbearing behavior?

149
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:20,000
It's to protect something.

150
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,760
It's because they have something to protect.

151
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:26,000
But I'll quit with no regrets.

152
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:30,600
I can't afford to waste my time on people like you anymore.

153
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:34,300
If the severance process doesn't go smoothly,

154
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:37,800
you'll see me in court with shackles.

155
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,500
Sit.

156
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,800
Come here.

157
00:11:50,290 --> 00:11:51,920
Hey!

158
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:54,770
I'll no longer tolerate it.

159
00:11:54,770 --> 00:11:58,010
You know how difficult a life Hyo Ri had, right?

160
00:11:58,010 --> 00:12:00,110
Why should she be sick?

161
00:12:00,110 --> 00:12:03,200
This is too unfair.

162
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,700
Thinking about it now,

163
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,800
I worked desperately to protect her.

164
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:10,170
But I couldn't be...

165
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,400
by her side when she needed me.

166
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,060
So, I'll stop living like that.

167
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:18,470
I won't be a pushover.

168
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,860
I'll fight all the injustices

169
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:25,100
and protect Hyo Ri right by her side.

170
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,400
Good job, Lee Ji An.

171
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:29,200
You know I'm a blue collar diner conglomerat, right?

172
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:32,300
I have no parents, siblings, or a husband.

173
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:35,600
I saved up a lot since I had nothing to spend on.

174
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,500
If we combine our savings,

175
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,930
we can easily pay for Hyo Ri's treatment.

176
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:41,800
Don't worry. You did a good thing.

177
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:44,950
Did you think I'd be moved by this?

178
00:12:44,950 --> 00:12:47,200
Whatever.

179
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:50,500
I couldn't call Hyo Ri.

180
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:53,440
I just couldn't for some reason.

181
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,890
Bring her back quickly because I miss her.

182
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:58,910
Okay. Hang up, Bitch.

183
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,180
Dad, hand me the wrench.

184
00:13:07,180 --> 00:13:08,820
Okay.

185
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,700
- Here.
- Thank you.

186
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,660
You make me uncomfortable by being here.

187
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:25,550
Why don't you check out the neighborhood?

188
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,100
Okay.

189
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:31,300
Dad,

190
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:34,000
go downtown. I bought the wrong wire.

191
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,900
It's the wrong size.

192
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:40,220
Why tell me that so secretly?

193
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:42,200
Because I would've looked lame.

194
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:45,200
Right. Men can't look lame.

195
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:49,200
I'll go without anyone noticing.

196
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,100
What's the deal?

197
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:05,200
It only took 30 minutes to circle around.

198
00:14:07,020 --> 00:14:08,880
It's so hot.

199
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:18,690
The empty fields get filled with stray dogs at night.

200
00:14:18,690 --> 00:14:23,300
Sometimes, they get into fights with boars.

201
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,700
Boar. Boar.

202
00:14:35,070 --> 00:14:36,640
Hey.

203
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:09,500
She looks very skillful.

204
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:15,240
These are basic skills you learn in school.

205
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,400
Are you okay?

206
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:27,000
Why am I here?

207
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,010
You overdressed to work in the field in this heat.

208
00:15:30,010 --> 00:15:32,400
Of course, you have heat exhaustion.

209
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:40,610
To tan the right amount for my physique,

210
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:44,400
I can't expose my skin to the sun.

211
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:49,500
But I can't give up on our garlic, either.

212
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:53,500
So, I had no choice...

213
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:58,500
but to work overdressed like this.

214
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:02,200
Gosh, my image was ruined.

215
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,600
You have no image to protect around here.

216
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:08,000
Don't try to save face and

217
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:12,300
try not to inconvenience others. Okay?

218
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:14,160
If it weren't for her,

219
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:17,150
you would've been eaten by stray dogs.

220
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:21,000
Do you feel dizzy or nauseous?

221
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:24,000
Drink water often, little by little,

222
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,090
and rest a while before moving.

223
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:28,100
Okay.

224
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:30,040
But you know...

225
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:33,300
are you a doctor or a nurse?

226
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:35,800
I was in medical school, but I quit.

227
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:38,100
I'm nothing anymore.

228
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:43,100
Go to the hospital if you feel sick after 30 minutes.

229
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,160
Okay.

230
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:46,640
Thank you.

231
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,870
Bye-bye.

232
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:49,990
Good work.

233
00:16:49,990 --> 00:16:52,770
Is she pretty and smart, too?

234
00:16:52,770 --> 00:16:54,440
Your eyesight is good at times like this.

235
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,850
It's no good.

236
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,700
Hello. How much are the apples?

237
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:22,680
They're 10,000 won for four.

238
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:26,100
- I see.
- Help yourself. They're tasty.

239
00:17:34,730 --> 00:17:36,230
Hello, Sir.

240
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:39,050
I'm looking for electrical wiring.

241
00:17:39,050 --> 00:17:41,550
Will the 5-meter one work?

242
00:17:48,830 --> 00:17:51,520
Goodness...

243
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:35,070
Oh, it hurts!

244
00:18:47,150 --> 00:18:50,100
Gosh, you're so out of touch.

245
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:55,010
Look. Anchorwoman Baek Ji Yeon was on the news with this hair.

246
00:18:55,010 --> 00:18:57,290
Gosh, when? When?

247
00:18:57,290 --> 00:18:59,150
Your faces are different.

248
00:18:59,150 --> 00:19:02,830
You'll look pathetic if you try to copy her.

249
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:04,940
What are you saying?

250
00:19:04,940 --> 00:19:07,060
Hey, look.

251
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,870
"As the recession continues,

252
00:19:10,870 --> 00:19:13,500
the market prices have been going up."

253
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:16,270
Hey, that's your problem.

254
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:18,700
You don't understand the basics.

255
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:21,000
A newscaster needs a mic.

256
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,200
You must do it properly.

257
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:27,800
Fine. If I held this...

258
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:30,620
"As the recession continues..."

259
00:19:55,610 --> 00:19:57,720
Are you okay?

260
00:19:57,720 --> 00:20:02,500
He doesn't have an accent.

261
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,900
He said, "Are you okay?"

262
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,640
Go in there!

263
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,690
Jeong Seok!

264
00:20:19,690 --> 00:20:22,290
Jeong Seok! Jeong Seok!

265
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:23,740
Hey!

266
00:20:23,740 --> 00:20:27,220
I thought the transfer student was a bookworm.

267
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:30,860
When did you steal a girl's heart?

268
00:20:30,860 --> 00:20:32,480
Wow!

269
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:34,380
Look.

270
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,810
- Hey, hold on—
- Hey!

271
00:20:37,810 --> 00:20:42,430
Jeong Seok's girlfriend is here! Oh my gosh!

272
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:46,840
What's she doing there?

273
00:21:13,670 --> 00:21:16,040
Geez, stop.

